huaweiSystemManMIB.name: huaweiSystemManMIB

revisions.description: Modified hwSysRebootReason. Add new reboot reason.
Modified hwSysCfgFileName description. hwSysCfgFileName is a string of 5 to 64 characters.
Add two hwIssuState: issuRollBackByUserCancel, issuRollBackByExceptional to hwIssuState.
Add one hwPatchErrorCode : patchMisoperation to hwPatchErrorType .
Add nodes for wlan ap upgrade.
Add two trap nodes hwSystemBoardExlude and hwSystemBoardExludeClear to huaweiSystemManMIBNotifications Table.
Add two trap nodes hwSysPafChangeNotification and hwSysLicenseChangeNotification to huaweiSystemManMIBNotifications Table.

huaweiSystemManMIB.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
huaweiSystemManMIB.description: The HUAWEI-SYS-MAN-MIB contains objects to manage the system. The module defines the information about system, such as system time, the current configuration file and system image file, system reload actions, and notifications. By querying the system time, configuration files and system image files, NMS can reboot the device in the specified time and the specified configuration and system image.

hwSysLocalClock.name: hwSysLocalClock
hwSysLocalClock.description: This object indicates the local time of the device.

hwSysCurTable.name: hwSysCurTable
hwSysCurTable.description: The current status of system. A configuration file and an image file are used to describe the current status.

hwSysCurEntry.name: hwSysCurEntry
hwSysCurEntry.description: An entry of hwSysCurTable. It is indexed by hwSysCurEntPhysicalIndex.

hwSysCurEntPhysicalIndex.name: hwSysCurEntPhysicalIndex
hwSysCurEntPhysicalIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the system index.

hwSysCurCFGFileIndex.name: hwSysCurCFGFileIndex
hwSysCurCFGFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the configuration file in the configuration file list. The value is referenced from hwSysCFGFileTable. The value ranges from 1 to 2147483647.

hwSysCurImageIndex.name: hwSysCurImageIndex
hwSysCurImageIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the image file in the image file list. The value is referenced from hwSysImageTable. The value ranges from 1 to 2147483647.

hwSysCurPafFileIndex.name: hwSysCurPafFileIndex
hwSysCurPafFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the PAF file in the PAF file list.

hwSysCurLicenseIndex.name: hwSysCurLicenseIndex
hwSysCurLicenseIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the license file in the license file list.

hwSysCurPatchFileIndex.name: hwSysCurPatchFileIndex
hwSysCurPatchFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the patch file in the patch file list.

hwSysCurVoiceFileIndex.name: hwSysCurVoiceFileIndex
hwSysCurVoiceFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the configuration file in the configuration file list. The value is referenced from hwSysCFGFileTable. The value ranges from 1 to 2147483647.

hwSysReloadSchedule.name: hwSysReloadSchedule
hwSysReloadSchedule.description: The value of this object identifies the record number used when the device restarts. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647. After the system restarts, the value returns to 0. 0: initial value. 65536: main board schedule method.

hwSysReloadAction.name: hwSysReloadAction
hwSysReloadAction.description: The value of this object identifies restart types. 1: reloadUnavailable 2: reloadOnSchedule, indicating periodical restart 3: reloadAtOnce, indicating immediate restart without considering hwSysReloadScheduleTime 4: reloadCancel, indicating that all the planned restart activities are cancelled. If hwSysReloadSchedule is invalid or the rows that hwSysReloadScheduleEntry and hwSysReloadSchedule point to are not activated, all the restart activities are ignored and an inconsistent value is returned. When the restart of the system is complete or no restart activities exist, the value of this object is reloadUnavailable(1).

hwSysReloadScheduleIndex.name: hwSysReloadScheduleIndex
hwSysReloadScheduleIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the instance. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647.

hwSysReloadEntity.name: hwSysReloadEntity
hwSysReloadEntity.description: This object indicates the index of the restarting entity. The value is referred to from entPhysicalTable. 1. When get/get-next, 1 means active main board, 2 means slave main board, 65535 means other board. 2. When set, 2 means slave main board, other values mean active main board.

hwSysReloadCfgFile.name: hwSysReloadCfgFile
hwSysReloadCfgFile.description: The value of this object identifies the configuration file used after the restart. The value is limited by hwSysCFGFileTable. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647. The default value is 0, which means the configuration file remains unchanged.

hwSysReloadImage.name: hwSysReloadImage
hwSysReloadImage.description: The value of this object identifies the image file used after the restart. The value is limited by hwSysImageTable. The value ranges from 1 to 2147483647.

hwSysReloadReason.name: hwSysReloadReason
hwSysReloadReason.description: This object indicates the cause of the restart. The value is a string of 0 to 255 characters. After the system restarts, the character string is deleted.

hwSysReloadScheduleTime.name: hwSysReloadScheduleTime
hwSysReloadScheduleTime.description: This object indicates the time of the restart. The only valid value of this object is an 8-byte string which indicates the local time of the switch. The maximum scheduled time is 30 days from the current system clock time. If the value set is earlier than the value of hwSysLocalClock or beyond the maximum scheduled time limit, a bad value error occurred. The value of all-zero octet strings indicates system restart at once if the reload action is reloadOnSchedule(1).

hwSysReloadRowStatus.name: hwSysReloadRowStatus
hwSysReloadRowStatus.description: If one of values of hwSysReloadEntity, hwSysReloadCfgFile and hwSysReloadImage is invalid, the value of hwSysReloadRowStatus cannot be set to 'active'. A valid entry means the specified element is available in the current system. Reload an entity indexed by hwSysReloadEntity with the startup configuration file and the image may be not allowed. Herein the entry is invalid.

hwSysReloadPafFile.name: hwSysReloadPafFile
hwSysReloadPafFile.description: The value of this object identifies the PAF file used after the restart.

hwSysReloadLicenseFile.name: hwSysReloadLicenseFile
hwSysReloadLicenseFile.description: The value of this object identifies the license file used after the restart.

hwSysReloadPatchFile.name: hwSysReloadPatchFile
hwSysReloadPatchFile.description: The value of this object identifies the patch file used after the restart.

hwSysReloadPatchState.name: hwSysReloadPatchState
hwSysReloadPatchState.description: The value of this object identifies the running status of the patch at the next startup. That is, whether the loaded patch is in the Run state at the next startup. run(1): indicates that the loaded patch is in the Run state at the next startup. unused(255): indicates that the loaded patch is in the original state at the next startup.

hwSysReloadOperateDestType.name: hwSysReloadOperateDestType
hwSysReloadOperateDestType.description: This object indicates the object to be restarted.

hwSysReloadOperateDestIndex.name: hwSysReloadOperateDestIndex
hwSysReloadOperateDestIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the board needs to be restarted. The get/get-next result is 'unused'. but, you can't use 'unused' to set.

hwSysReloadVoiceFile.name: hwSysReloadVoiceFile
hwSysReloadVoiceFile.description: The value of this object identifies the license file used after the restart.

hwSysReloadAndroidFile.name: hwSysReloadAndroidFile
hwSysReloadAndroidFile.description: The value of this object identifies the android file used after the restart. The value is limited by hwSysAndroidFileTable. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647. The default value is 0, which means the android file remains unchanged.

hwSysReboot.name: hwSysReboot
hwSysReboot.description: The value of this object identifies the restart of the master and slave boards. Values are as follows unused(1): indicates that this value is not used. Generally, this value is read. rebootAllRoute(2): indicates that the integrated device is restarted. rebootSlave(3): indicates that the slave board is restarted. slaveSwitch(4): indicates that the switchover between the main and slave boards is performed.

hwSysSlaveSwitchEnable.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchEnable
hwSysSlaveSwitchEnable.description: The value of this object identifies whether the switchover between the main and the slave boards is enabled. enable(1): indicates that the switchover between the main and slave boards is enabled. disable(2): indicates that the switchover between the main and slave boards is not enabled.

hwSysLatestRebootErrorInfo.name: hwSysLatestRebootErrorInfo
hwSysLatestRebootErrorInfo.description: This object indicates the cause of the last restart.

hwSysSlaveSwitchTable.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchTable
hwSysSlaveSwitchTable.description: A slave switchover enable parameters table.

hwSysSlaveSwitchIndex.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchIndex
hwSysSlaveSwitchIndex.description: The value of the object identifies the index of the table.

hwSysSlaveSwitchChassisNum.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchChassisNum
hwSysSlaveSwitchChassisNum.description: The value of the object identifies the chassis number.

hwSysSlaveSwitchOperType.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchOperType
hwSysSlaveSwitchOperType.description: Operation type. The object has the following values: unused(1): means the default value. slaveswitch(2): perform force switchover. slaveswitchlock(3): enable the force switchover, this value should be used with the object of hwSysSlaveSwitchEnableStatus.

hwSysSlaveSwitchEnableStatus.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchEnableStatus
hwSysSlaveSwitchEnableStatus.description: The enable status of switchover for AMB (Active Main Board) and SMB (Standby Main Board). enable(1): enable the force switchover. disable(2): disable the force switchover.

hwSysSlaveSwitchSrc.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchSrc
hwSysSlaveSwitchSrc.description: The source slot for slave switchover.

hwSysSlaveSwitchDst.name: hwSysSlaveSwitchDst
hwSysSlaveSwitchDst.description: The destination slot for slave switchover.

hwSysDelayReboot.name: hwSysDelayReboot
hwSysDelayReboot.description: Restart the device at a delayed time. The delayed time can be set up to 43200 minutes. The node is used to set the delayed time, cancel the setting, or check the status of the delayed restart. If a value within the range of 0 to 43200 is entered, the delayed time is set. If the value 65535 is entered, the setting is cancelled. During system reboot, a return value 65534 is displayed if the Get or Walk operation is performed. Other values are invalid.

hwSysImageNum.name: hwSysImageNum
hwSysImageNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of image files. The object calculates the number of image files given by hwSysImageTable. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647.

hwSysImageEntry.name: hwSysImageEntry
hwSysImageEntry.description: A system image entry. Each entry consists of information of a system image. hwSysImageIndex exclusively decides an image file.

hwSysImageIndex.name: hwSysImageIndex
hwSysImageIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the image file.

hwSysImageName.name: hwSysImageName
hwSysImageName.description: This object indicates the name of the image file. A file name containing path and suffix is a string of 4 to 64 characters.

hwSysImageSize.name: hwSysImageSize
hwSysImageSize.description: The value of this object identifies the size of the image file. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647, in bytes. The size depends on the actual file and is limited by the physical storage device.

hwSysImageLocation.name: hwSysImageLocation
hwSysImageLocation.description: This object indicates the location of the image file, namely the path.

hwSysImageVersion.name: hwSysImageVersion
hwSysImageVersion.description: The value of this object identifies the version of the image file.

hwSysImageReason.name: hwSysImageReason
hwSysImageReason.description: The value of this object identifies the error cause of the image file.

hwSysCFGFileNum.name: hwSysCFGFileNum
hwSysCFGFileNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of configuration files. The object calculates the number of configuration files given by hwSysCFGFileTable. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647.

hwSysCFGFileTable.name: hwSysCFGFileTable
hwSysCFGFileTable.description: A table of configuration files in this system.

hwSysCFGFileEntry.name: hwSysCFGFileEntry
hwSysCFGFileEntry.description: A configuration file entry. Each entry consists of information of a configuration file. hwSysCFGFileIndex exclusively decides a configuration file.

hwSysCFGFileIndex.name: hwSysCFGFileIndex
hwSysCFGFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the configuration file.

hwSysCFGFileName.name: hwSysCFGFileName
hwSysCFGFileName.description: This object indicates the name of the configuration file. Currently, Huawei products support two formats of configuration files, namely, .CFG and .ZIP. A file name containing path and suffix is a string of 5 to 64 characters.

hwSysCFGFileSize.name: hwSysCFGFileSize
hwSysCFGFileSize.description: The value of this object identifies the size of the configuration file. The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647.

hwSysCFGFileLocation.name: hwSysCFGFileLocation
hwSysCFGFileLocation.description: This object indicates the location of the configuration file, namely, the path.

hwSysCFGFileReason.name: hwSysCFGFileReason
hwSysCFGFileReason.description: This object indicates the error cause of the configuration file.

hwSysPafFileNum.name: hwSysPafFileNum
hwSysPafFileNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of PAF files in the system.

hwSysPafFileTable.name: hwSysPafFileTable
hwSysPafFileTable.description: A table of paf files in this system.

hwSysPafFileEntry.name: hwSysPafFileEntry
hwSysPafFileEntry.description: A paf file entry. Each entry consists of information of a paf file. hwSysPafFileIndex exclusively decides a configuration file.

hwSysPafFileIndex.name: hwSysPafFileIndex
hwSysPafFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of this table.

hwSysPafFileName.name: hwSysPafFileName
hwSysPafFileName.description: This object indicates the name of the PAF file.

hwSysPafFileSize.name: hwSysPafFileSize
hwSysPafFileSize.description: The value of this object identifies the size of the PAF file.

hwSysPafFileLocation.name: hwSysPafFileLocation
hwSysPafFileLocation.description: This object indicates the position of the PAF file.

hwSysPafFileVersion.name: hwSysPafFileVersion
hwSysPafFileVersion.description: This object indicates the version of the PAF file.

hwSysLicenseFileNum.name: hwSysLicenseFileNum
hwSysLicenseFileNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of license files in the system.

hwSysLicenseFileTable.name: hwSysLicenseFileTable
hwSysLicenseFileTable.description: A table of license files in this system.

hwSysLicenseFileEntry.name: hwSysLicenseFileEntry
hwSysLicenseFileEntry.description: A license file entry. Each entry consists of information of a license file. hwSysLicenseFileIndex exclusively decides a configuration file.

hwSysLicenseFileIndex.name: hwSysLicenseFileIndex
hwSysLicenseFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of this table.

hwSysLicenseFileName.name: hwSysLicenseFileName
hwSysLicenseFileName.description: This object indicates the name of the license file.

hwSysLicenseFileSize.name: hwSysLicenseFileSize
hwSysLicenseFileSize.description: This object indicates the size of the license file.

hwSysLicenseFileLocation.name: hwSysLicenseFileLocation
hwSysLicenseFileLocation.description: This object indicates the position of the license file.

hwPatchFileNum.name: hwPatchFileNum
hwPatchFileNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of patches in the system.

hwPatchRecordReset.name: hwPatchRecordReset
hwPatchRecordReset.description: Clear the patch records. unused(1): unused. resetPatchHistory(2): clears the hwPatchHistoryTable record. resetPatchError(3): clears the hwPatchErrorTable record.

hwPatchTrapEnble.name: hwPatchTrapEnble
hwPatchTrapEnble.description: The value of this object determines whether to generate the trap of HUAWEI-SYS-MAN-MIB. enable(1): Trap is enabled. disable(2): Trap is not enabled.

hwPatchErrorTableMax.name: hwPatchErrorTableMax
hwPatchErrorTableMax.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum number of recorded errors supported by hwPatchErrorTable.

hwPatchId.name: hwPatchId
hwPatchId.description: This object indicates the patch ID on the device.

hwPatchLatestId.name: hwPatchLatestId
hwPatchLatestId.description: This object indicates the latest patch ID on the device.

hwPatchFailReason.name: hwPatchFailReason
hwPatchFailReason.description: This object is an index that specifies patch fail reason.

hwPatchFileEntry.name: hwPatchFileEntry
hwPatchFileEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwPatchFileTable.

hwPatchFileIndex.name: hwPatchFileIndex
hwPatchFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of this table.

hwPatchFileName.name: hwPatchFileName
hwPatchFileName.description: This object indicates the name of a patch file.

hwPatchFileSize.name: hwPatchFileSize
hwPatchFileSize.description: This object indicates the size of a patch file.

hwPatchFileLocation.name: hwPatchFileLocation
hwPatchFileLocation.description: This object indicates the position of a patch file.

hwPatchFileVersion.name: hwPatchFileVersion
hwPatchFileVersion.description: This object indicates the version of the patch file.

hwLoadPatchTable.name: hwLoadPatchTable
hwLoadPatchTable.description: The load table of the patch file. Load the patch file to the memory: hwSlotIndex:The slot ID of the destination device to be loaded by the patch file, hwPatchFileIndex:The index of the patch file, If hwSlotIndex is 128, it indicates all slots of the device.

hwLoadPatchEntry.name: hwLoadPatchEntry
hwLoadPatchEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwLoadPatchTable.

hwPatchLoadDestType.name: hwPatchLoadDestType
hwPatchLoadDestType.description: This object indicates the type of the board to be loaded with the patch.

hwPatchLoadDestIndex.name: hwPatchLoadDestIndex
hwPatchLoadDestIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the board to be loaded with the patch.

hwPatchLoadState.name: hwPatchLoadState
hwPatchLoadState.description: Patch loading state: loading(1):Patch is loading. success(2):Patch loading succeeded. failure(3):Patch loading failed. none(4):Patch and board do not match.

hwLoadPatchRowState.name: hwLoadPatchRowState
hwLoadPatchRowState.description: This object identifies the status of a row.

hwPatchTable.name: hwPatchTable
hwPatchTable.description: Running status transfer and query of the patch. If hwSlotIndex is 128, it indicates all slots of the device. If hwPatchNum is 65535, it indicates all patches of the specified slot. If hwPatchNum is 0, it indicates the NP patch of the specified slot. If hwPatchNum is in range from 1 to 200, it indicates the C patch of the specified slot.

hwPatchEntry.name: hwPatchEntry
hwPatchEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwPatchTable.

hwPatchSlotIndex.name: hwPatchSlotIndex
hwPatchSlotIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the slot.

hwPatchIndex.name: hwPatchIndex
hwPatchIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the patch.

hwPatchUsedFileName.name: hwPatchUsedFileName
hwPatchUsedFileName.description: This object indicates the name of the patch file.

hwPatchVersion.name: hwPatchVersion
hwPatchVersion.description: This object indicates the version of the patch file.

hwPatchDescription.name: hwPatchDescription
hwPatchDescription.description: This object indicates the description of the patch.

hwPatchProgramVersion.name: hwPatchProgramVersion
hwPatchProgramVersion.description: The value of the object identifies the version number of the host software.

hwPatchFuncNum.name: hwPatchFuncNum
hwPatchFuncNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number functions contained in the patch.

hwPatchTextLen.name: hwPatchTextLen
hwPatchTextLen.description: The value of this object identifies the length of the patch code.

hwPatchDataLen.name: hwPatchDataLen
hwPatchDataLen.description: The value of this object identifies the length of the patch data.

hwPatchType.name: hwPatchType
hwPatchType.description: The value of this object identifies the patch type. hotCommon(1): indicates the common hot patch. hotTemporary(2): indicates the temporary hot patch. coolCommon(3): indicates the common cool patch. coolTemporary(4): indicates the temporary cool patch.

hwPatchBuildTime.name: hwPatchBuildTime
hwPatchBuildTime.description: This object indicates the time when a patch file is built.

hwPatchActiveTime.name: hwPatchActiveTime
hwPatchActiveTime.description: This object indicates the time when a patch file is activated.

hwPatchAdminStatus.name: hwPatchAdminStatus
hwPatchAdminStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the operation status of a patch. Run (1): indicates that the patch status is Run. Active(2): indicates the patch status is Active. Deactive(3): indicates the patch status is Deactive. Delete(4): indicates that the patch is deleted.

hwPatchOperateState.name: hwPatchOperateState
hwPatchOperateState.description: status of the patch. patchRunning(1): indicates that current status of the patch is Run. patchActive(2): indicates that current status of the patch is Active. patchDeactive(3): indicates that current status of the patch is Deactive.

hwPatchOperateDestType.name: hwPatchOperateDestType
hwPatchOperateDestType.description: Patch operate object type,it combine with the hwPatchOperateDestIndex to note the operate object.

hwPatchOperateDestIndex.name: hwPatchOperateDestIndex
hwPatchOperateDestIndex.description: Patch operate object index,it combine with chassis,the value of the hwPatchOperateDestType to note the operate object.hwPatchOperateDestIndex is value such as ccc1,clc2 etc.

hwPatchStateTable.name: hwPatchStateTable
hwPatchStateTable.description: The statistics information of the C patch area on each slot.

hwPatchStateEntry.name: hwPatchStateEntry
hwPatchStateEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwPatchStateTable.

hwPatchNumMax.name: hwPatchNumMax
hwPatchNumMax.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum number of patches.

hwPatchIdleNum.name: hwPatchIdleNum
hwPatchIdleNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of idle patches.

hwPatchTextMax.name: hwPatchTextMax
hwPatchTextMax.description: The value of this object identifies the size of the code in the patch area.

hwPatchDataMax.name: hwPatchDataMax
hwPatchDataMax.description: The value of this object identifies the size of the data in the patch area.

hwPatchStateTextUsed.name: hwPatchStateTextUsed
hwPatchStateTextUsed.description: The value of this object identifies the size of the used code in the patch area.

hwPatchStateDataUsed.name: hwPatchStateDataUsed
hwPatchStateDataUsed.description: The value of this object identifies the size of the used data in the patch area.

hwPatchStateTotalPatchNum.name: hwPatchStateTotalPatchNum
hwPatchStateTotalPatchNum.description: The value of this object identifies the total number of used patches.

hwPatchStateTempPatchNum.name: hwPatchStateTempPatchNum
hwPatchStateTempPatchNum.description: The value of this object identifies the total number of used temporary patches.

hwPatchStateCommonPatchNum.name: hwPatchStateCommonPatchNum
hwPatchStateCommonPatchNum.description: The value of this object identifies the total number of used common patches.

hwPatchStateRuningPatchNum.name: hwPatchStateRuningPatchNum
hwPatchStateRuningPatchNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of patches in the Run state in the patch area.

hwPatchStateActivePatchNum.name: hwPatchStateActivePatchNum
hwPatchStateActivePatchNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of patches in the Active state in the patch area.

hwPatchStateDeactivePatchNum.name: hwPatchStateDeactivePatchNum
hwPatchStateDeactivePatchNum.description: The value of this object identifies the number of patches in the Deactive state in the patch area.

hwPatchHistoryEntry.name: hwPatchHistoryEntry
hwPatchHistoryEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwPatchHistoryTable.

hwPatchHistoryIndex.name: hwPatchHistoryIndex
hwPatchHistoryIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the table.

hwPatchHistoryProgrameVersion.name: hwPatchHistoryProgrameVersion
hwPatchHistoryProgrameVersion.description: The value of the object identifies the version number of the image file.

hwPatchHistoryVersion.name: hwPatchHistoryVersion
hwPatchHistoryVersion.description: The value of this object identifies the version of the patch.

hwSlotId.name: hwSlotId
hwSlotId.description: The value of the object identifies the slot number of the patch.

hwPatchBeginIndex.name: hwPatchBeginIndex
hwPatchBeginIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the start ID of the loaded patch.

hwPatchEndIndex.name: hwPatchEndIndex
hwPatchEndIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the end ID of the loaded patch.

hwPatchHistoryAction.name: hwPatchHistoryAction
hwPatchHistoryAction.description: The value of this object identifies the patch status.

hwPatchHistoryBeginTime.name: hwPatchHistoryBeginTime
hwPatchHistoryBeginTime.description: This object indicates the start time of running the patch.

hwPatchHistoryEndTime.name: hwPatchHistoryEndTime
hwPatchHistoryEndTime.description: This object indicates the end time of running the patch.

hwPatchErrorTable.name: hwPatchErrorTable
hwPatchErrorTable.description: The error record table of patch operation.

hwPatchErrorEntry.name: hwPatchErrorEntry
hwPatchErrorEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwPatchErrorTable.

hwPatchErrorIndex.name: hwPatchErrorIndex
hwPatchErrorIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the patch error.

hwPatchErrorSlot.name: hwPatchErrorSlot
hwPatchErrorSlot.description: This object indicates the number of the slot related to a patch error.

hwPatchErrorPatchFileName.name: hwPatchErrorPatchFileName
hwPatchErrorPatchFileName.description: This object indicates the index of the patch file when the patch has an error.

hwPatchErrorPatchIndex.name: hwPatchErrorPatchIndex
hwPatchErrorPatchIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the patch when the patch has an error.

hwPatchErrorCode.name: hwPatchErrorCode
hwPatchErrorCode.description: This object indicates the flag of the patch error.

hwBootRomTable.name: hwBootRomTable
hwBootRomTable.description: Boot ROM startup parameter query table.

hwBootRomEntry.name: hwBootRomEntry
hwBootRomEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwBootRomTable.

hwBootRomIndex.name: hwBootRomIndex
hwBootRomIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of the BootROM table.

hwBootRomBootDevice.name: hwBootRomBootDevice
hwBootRomBootDevice.description: This object indicates the name of the BootROM startup device.

hwBootRomProcessorNo.name: hwBootRomProcessorNo
hwBootRomProcessorNo.description: The value of this object identifies the number of the BootROM processor.

hwBootRomHostName.name: hwBootRomHostName
hwBootRomHostName.description: The object indicates the name of the BootROM host.

hwBootRomFileName.name: hwBootRomFileName
hwBootRomFileName.description: The object indicates the name of the BootROM file.

hwBootRomIpOnEthernet.name: hwBootRomIpOnEthernet
hwBootRomIpOnEthernet.description: The object indicates the IP address of the BootROM Ethernet interface.

hwBootRomIpOnBackPlane.name: hwBootRomIpOnBackPlane
hwBootRomIpOnBackPlane.description: The object indicates the IP address of the BootROM backplane.

hwBootRomHostIp.name: hwBootRomHostIp
hwBootRomHostIp.description: The object indicates the IP address of the BootROM host.

hwBootRomGatewayIp.name: hwBootRomGatewayIp
hwBootRomGatewayIp.description: The object indicates the IP address of the BootROM gateway.

hwBootRomUserName.name: hwBootRomUserName
hwBootRomUserName.description: The object indicates the name of the BootROM user.

hwBootRomPassword.name: hwBootRomPassword
hwBootRomPassword.description: The object indicates the BootROM password.

hwBootRomTargetName.name: hwBootRomTargetName
hwBootRomTargetName.description: The object indicates the name of the BootROM target.

hwBootRomStartupScript.name: hwBootRomStartupScript
hwBootRomStartupScript.description: The object indicates the BootROM startup script.

hwBootRomXModemBaudRate.name: hwBootRomXModemBaudRate
hwBootRomXModemBaudRate.description: The value of the object identifies the baud rate for transmitting the XModem data.

hwSysUpgradeEntry.name: hwSysUpgradeEntry
hwSysUpgradeEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwSysUpgradeTable.

hwIssuImageFile.name: hwIssuImageFile
hwIssuImageFile.description: The name of the image file.

hwIssuPafFile.name: hwIssuPafFile
hwIssuPafFile.description: The name of the paf file.

hwIssuLicenseFile.name: hwIssuLicenseFile
hwIssuLicenseFile.description: The name of the license file.

hwIssuPatchFile.name: hwIssuPatchFile
hwIssuPatchFile.description: The name of the patch file.

hwIssuConditionCheck.name: hwIssuConditionCheck
hwIssuConditionCheck.description: System issu upgrade condition check. The default check result is normal.

hwSysSourceIndexEntry.name: hwSysSourceIndexEntry
hwSysSourceIndexEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hwBootRomTable.

hwSysFileType.name: hwSysFileType
hwSysFileType.description: The value of this object is an index that indicates the type of a file.

hwSysFileName.name: hwSysFileName
hwSysFileName.description: This object is an index that indicates the name of a file on the main control board.

hwSysFileIndex.name: hwSysFileIndex
hwSysFileIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of a file in the specified table. If the value is 0, it indicates that this file does not exist in the specified table.

hwSysRebootTimes.name: hwSysRebootTimes
hwSysRebootTimes.description: The value of the device reboot times.

hwSysRebootTime.name: hwSysRebootTime
hwSysRebootTime.description: The time at which the reboot action occurred. we will only take octet strings with length 8 for this object which indicates the local time of the switch. The maximum scheduled time is 30 days from the current system clock time. field octets contents range 1 1-2 year 0..65536 2 3 month 1..12 3 4 day 1..31 4 5 hour 0..23 5 6 minutes 0..59 6 7 seconds 0..60 (use 60 for leap-second) 7 8 deci-seconds 0..9
